<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students from cooperating high schools can earn up to 15 hours (with no more than six hours or
two courses in one subject matter area) through the College Board's (CEEB's) Advanced
Placement Testing Program. Credit is awarded for scores of 3 or above. The awarding of credit
will be administrated by the Registrar's Office with the appropriate approval of the Vice President
for Academic Affairs.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.alcorn.edu/Academics/default.aspx?id=5667" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

